## Vercel Speed Insights Installation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the Next.js project following the official documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart.

### Changes Made:

**1. Package Installation:**
- Installed `@vercel/speed-insights` v2.0.0 using npm
- Updated `package.json` with the new dependency
- Updated `package-lock.json` with resolved dependencies

**2. Code Integration:**
- Modified `app/layout.tsx` to add the SpeedInsights component
- Added import statement: `import { SpeedInsights } from '@vercel/speed-insights/next'`
- Added `<SpeedInsights />` component inside the `<body>` tag, after the MotionProvider wrapper
- Placement follows Next.js App Router best practices (v16.1.6)

### Files Modified:
- `app/layout.tsx` - Added SpeedInsights import and component
- `package.json` - Added @vercel/speed-insights dependency
- `package-lock.json` - Updated with new package dependencies

### Implementation Details:
- Used the framework-specific Next.js import path (`@vercel/speed-insights/next`)
- Component is placed at the end of the body to avoid interfering with existing layout structure
- No environment variables or additional configuration required
- The component is automatically enabled and will collect performance metrics when deployed to Vercel

### Verification:
✅ Build completed successfully with no errors
✅ Linter passed with no issues
✅ TypeScript compilation successful
✅ All static pages generated correctly (12/12 pages)

### Next Steps for Deployment:
1. Push the changes to the repository
2. Deploy to Vercel (automatic deployment via Git connection)
3. Enable Speed Insights in the Vercel dashboard under the project's Speed Insights section
4. Performance metrics will begin collecting automatically after deployment

### Notes:
- Speed Insights works seamlessly with the existing project structure
- No conflicts with existing dependencies (framer-motion, next, react, etc.)
- The component is lightweight and won't impact page load performance
- Data collection is automatic and requires no additional setup after deployment
